{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-03-01T04:38:12.661Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file-1772339892661-8818ebcee2336","parameters":{"content":"# Cloned Repositories\n\nThis directory contains research implementations related to thinking tokens and reasoning in LLMs.\n\n## 1. Quiet-STaR (ezelikman/quiet-star)\n- **Purpose**: Implementation of \"Quiet-STaR: Language Models Can Teach Themselves to Think Before Speaking\".\n- **Key Idea**: Generates rationales at each token to explain future text.\n- **Location**: `code/quiet-star/`\n\n## 2. Filler Tokens (rokosbasilisk/filler-tokens)\n- **Purpose**: Implementation of \"Let's Think Dot by Dot: Hidden Computation in Transformer Language Models\".\n- **Key Idea**: Investigates the use of meaningless filler tokens (e.g., '......') for hidden computation.\n- **Location**: `code/filler-tokens/`\n\n## 3. Pause Token (epfl-dlab/PauseToken)\n- **Purpose**: Implementation of \"Learning to Insert [PAUSE] Tokens for Better Reasoning\".\n- **Key Idea**: Methods for inserting [PAUSE] tokens to improve reasoning performance.\n- **Location**: `code/pause-token/`\n","file_path":"code/README.md"}}
